window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>The protector is spiraling, and I'm his anchor.</b></p> <p>Life at Kingston University has only gotten worse. Secrets, lies, and death surround SIN. But nothing is as it seems.</p> <p>We each have pasts that haunt us; our futures are uncertain.</p> <p>One thing is clear, these brutal boys of SIN will protect me—and Chase—with their lives. But I'm terrified I'll lose them as our unknown enemy tracks closer. Someone is determined to take away our newfound happiness.</p> <p>One fierce defender. One possessive guardian. One unrelenting voyeur.</p> <p>Wilder.</p> <p>Royal.</p> <p>Beckham.</p> <p>As the danger escalates, so does our anxiety over the threats against us. And with no one to turn to for guidance, everything begins to unravel… until assistance appears from a surprising source.</p> <p>Sigma Iota Nu. Where existing bonds are broken, and our new life begins.</p> <p>Wilder <i>is the final book in the Brutal Boys of SIN trilogy, centering around three men and one woman. MMMF. This should be listened to after the Brothers of Hawthorne Hall trilogy and Bastards of Bainbridge Hall trilogy, as they are connected. For mature listeners.</i></p>"; 
